From 93114dfdcd9d4ad60dcdae4eacdd61c87881f871 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 08:13:57 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 59/90] ntfs: fix mmap_prepare writable check for shared
 mappings

Linus pointed out that checking only VMA_WRITE_BIT is incorrect.
Private writable mappings (MAP_PRIVATE) set VM_WRITE but do not
write back to the filesystem. Also, mappings that can become
writable via mprotect() (VM_MAYWRITE) must be handled.

Use vma_desc_test_all(VMA_SHARED_BIT, VMA_MAYWRITE_BIT) instead,
which matches what other filesystems do.

[ naim: Use vma_desc_test_flags() twice because vma_desc_test_all is not
  available in 7.0 ]

Suggested-by: Linus Torvalds <torvalds@linux-foundation.org>
Reviewed-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Eric Naim <dnaim@cachyos.org>
---
 fs/ntfs/file.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/ntfs/file.c b/fs/ntfs/file.c
index 967d43c23..15e9dc9bf 100644
--- a/fs/ntfs/file.c
+++ b/fs/ntfs/file.c
@@ -644,7 +644,8 @@ static int ntfs_file_mmap_prepare(struct vm_area_desc *desc)
 	if (NInoCompressed(NTFS_I(inode)))
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
-	if (vma_desc_test_flags(desc, VMA_WRITE_BIT)) {
+	if (vma_desc_test_flags(desc, VMA_SHARED_BIT) &&
+	    vma_desc_test_flags(desc, VMA_MAYWRITE_BIT)) {
 		struct inode *inode = file_inode(file);
 		loff_t from, to;
 		int err;
-- 
